史蒂文·威尔逊谈新专辑《The Harmony Codex》：“我很荣幸基本上可以做我想做的事” https://www.nme.com/news/music/steven-wilson-interview-harmony-codex-economies-scale-manic-street-preachers-porcupine-tree-3490247?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=steven-wilson-访谈和谐法典经济规模躁狂街头传教士豪猪树John EarlsTue, 29 Aug 2023 11:02:55 +0000 Music InterviewsMusic NewsNewsRockhttps://www.nme.com/?p=3490247 <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/STEVEN-WILSON-BY-HAJO-MUELLER_2000.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="史蒂文·威尔逊.图片来源：哈乔·穆勒" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/STEVEN-WILSON-BY-HAJO-MUELLER_2000.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/STEVEN-WILSON-BY-HAJO-MUELLER_2000-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/STEVEN-WILSON-BY-HAJO-MUELLER_2000-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/STEVEN-WILSON-BY-HAJO-MUELLER_2000-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/STEVEN-WILSON-BY-HAJO-MUELLER_2000-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/STEVEN-WILSON-BY-HAJO-MUELLER_2000-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p>看看 Porcupine Tree 主唱新专辑中的“Economies Of Scale”，其中收录了 Manic Street Preachers、Interpol、Radiophonic Workshop、Opeth 和 Tears For Fears 的混音作品</p><p><a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/steven-wilson-interview-harmony-codex-economies-scale-manic-street-preachers-porcupine-tree-3490247">史蒂文·威尔逊 (Steven Wilson) 在新专辑“The Harmony Codex”上发表的帖子：“我很荣幸基本上可以做我想做的事”，</a>首先出现在<a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a>上。</p> ; <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/STEVEN-WILSON-BY-HAJO-MUELLER_2000.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="史蒂文·威尔逊.图片来源：哈乔·穆勒" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/STEVEN-WILSON-BY-HAJO-MUELLER_2000.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/STEVEN-WILSON-BY-HAJO-MUELLER_2000-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/STEVEN-WILSON-BY-HAJO-MUELLER_2000-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/STEVEN-WILSON-BY-HAJO-MUELLER_2000-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/STEVEN-WILSON-BY-HAJO-MUELLER_2000-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/STEVEN-WILSON-BY-HAJO-MUELLER_2000-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p><a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/porcupine-tree">豪猪树</a>歌手兼多乐器演奏家<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/steven-wilson">史蒂文·威尔逊（Steven Wilson）</a>宣布了他的新个人专辑“The Harmony Codex”。请查看下面的新单曲“规模经济”，以及我们对艺术家的采访。</p><ul><li> <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/porcupine-tree-rats-return-video-steve-wilson-interview-tour-tickets-3249892"><strong>阅读更多：</strong>豪猪树：“我们是典型的邪教乐队”</a></li></ul><p> 《The Harmony Codex》豪华三碟版于 9 月 29 日发行，其中包括<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/MANIC-STREET-PREACHERS">Manic Street Preachers</a> 、 <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/interpol">Interpol</a> 、 <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/tears-for-fears">Tears For Fears</a>的 Roland Orzabal、Opeth 的 Mikael Akerfeldt 和电子音乐先驱 Radiophonic Workshop 等人的歌曲混音版。</p><p> 《The Harmony Codex》已在伦敦、纽约、柏林、洛杉矶和阿姆斯特丹等城市为粉丝举办了试听会。 “这张专辑的大部分内容都是根据完全沉浸式环境中的感觉来构思的，”威尔逊解释道。 “我想要尽可能多地沉浸式预览《The Harmony Codex》，因为人们很少能在黑暗中不受干扰地聆听专辑。他们真的很享受这种感觉：‘哦，是的，这就是我们过去听音乐的方式！’”</p><p>第一首单曲“Economies Of Scale”现已与曾执导过《Jungle》和《Everything But The Girl》的查理·迪·帕蒂诺 (Charlie Di Patino) 制作的视频一起发行。 </p><p><iframe loading="lazy" title="史蒂文·威尔逊 - 规模经济" width="696" height="392" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/wmtyvKz8ubQ?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><p></p><p> 《The Harmony Codex》是继 Porcupine Tree 12 年来首张专辑《Closure/Continuation》之后推出的，该专辑于 2022 年在英国排名第二， <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/porcupine-tree-on-course-for-this-weeks-number-one-album-3257875">仅被 Harry Styles 的《Harry&#39;s House》挤在榜首</a>。该三人组还包括理查德·巴比耶里 (Richard Barbieri) 和加文·哈里森 (Gavin Harrison)，他们在专辑巡演中以温布利体育场 (Wembley Arena) 为主题，巡演于 8 月 5 日在德国音乐节 Rock Im Park 结束。</p><p> Wilson 的第八张个人专辑《The Harmony Codex》继 2021 年的《The Future Bites》之后， <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/listen-to-biffy-clyros-mechanised-remix-of-steven-wilsons-personal-shopper-2966970">由 Elton John</a> 、 <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/MYSTERY-JETS">Mystery Jets</a> 、 <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/enter-shikari">Enter Shikari</a>和<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/the-cure">The Cure</a>鼓手 Jason Cooper 主演，并在英国排名第四。</p><p> “The Harmony Codex”的其他嘉宾包括 Interpol 鼓手 Sam Fogarino、舞蹈/嘻哈老将 Meat Beat Manifesto 的 Jack Dangers、Kneebody 鼓手 Nate Wood 以及威尔逊的长期合作伙伴 Ninet Tayeb、Craig Blundell 和 Adam Holzman。</p><p>除了他自己的音乐之外，Wilson 还因其为其他艺术家的经典专辑制作的空间混音而闻名，包括 Roxy Music、Suede、Chic、ABC 和 Guns N&#39; Roses。 “作为那个场景的一部分，我觉得我应该尝试制作一张自己的专辑，以提高空间音频的可能性，”威尔逊告诉<em>NME</em> 。</p><p>现场表演尚未公布，威尔逊计划在私密场所进行一系列驻场表演，而不是传统的巡演。 “我想将身临其境的感觉带入现场场景，并在更小的房间里演奏，也许可以容纳 600 人，”Wilson 说。 “我会安装一个令人惊叹的空间音频系统，然后通过灯光装置和投影让观众进入乐队内部。我想创造一个可以进行表演的环境。”</p><p> To launch the new album, Wilson also told <em>NME</em> of his amazement at persuading Manic Street Preachers to do a remix, why he&#39;s finally comfortable at doing what he wants and whether Porcupine Tree still have a future…</p><h3> <strong>NME: Hi, Steven. What was the starting point for your new album?</strong></h3><p> <strong>Wilson</strong> : “I had a book out last year, &#39;Limited Edition Of One&#39;. Some chapters were about my relationship with fans, some were just lists of books, movies and songs that inspired me. I finished the book with a short story, <em>The Harmony Codex</em> . It was dystopian sci-fi and, like a lot of my music, it had a very dreamlike quality.</p><p> “As I was writing the story, I was beginning to develop the initial ideas for this record. It felt logical to have a narrative feel to the songs, to match the cinematic quality of the music. It made sense to write an imaginary soundtrack for that short story, writing music based on its characters and ideas.”</p><h3> <strong>&#39;The Harmony Codex&#39; is very eclectic, with acoustic songs like &#39;Time Is Running Out&#39; alongside the lengthy and largely instrumental title track. Was that variety intended from the outset?</strong></h3><p> “I didn&#39;t want any sense of agenda for the album. I didn&#39;t want it sound like any particular type of record. I wanted to go with what felt right. The title track being a 10 minute ambient piece in the middle of the album, on previous records I&#39;d probably have said to myself: &#39;You can&#39;t do that. People aren&#39;t going to go with it.&#39;</p><p> “Maybe due to lockdown&#39;s enforced isolation, I had a very different mindset on this record. I wanted a record that would wrongfoot you, almost confuse you by keeping you guessing. I hope it keeps people surprised.”</p><h3> <strong>It must help that your fanbase are probably used to you surprising them by now…</strong></h3><p> “绝对地。 Part of this record is confidence from having done this for a long time now, which means I can think: &#39;No, fuck it, I can put a 10-minute ambient piece on the same record as an acoustic song and an electronic pop song.&#39; It&#39;s good to embrace that.</p><p> “I don&#39;t underestimate how lucky and privileged I am to be able to do this, basically doing what the fuck I want. I don&#39;t think many musicians can say that these days. I still confront the expectations of my audience. I rarely give them what they want or expect, yet somehow I take a lot of them with me. I&#39;m grateful that it&#39;s how my career has panned out.”</p><h3> <strong>Why was the spatial audio aspect of the album important for you?</strong></h3><p> “Dolby Atmos has become significant in the industry in the last three years, since Apple and Amazon adopted it. That aspect was how I approached recording and mixing, not the writing of the record. I think I&#39;m pretty good at not getting caught up in the technical issues of spatial audio: I still have a very visceral emotional approach to the music I&#39;m making.” </p><blockquote class="instagram-media" data-instgrm-captioned data-instgrm-permalink="https://www.instagram.com/p/Cv7lFdDoiFL/?utm_source=ig_embed&amp;utm_campaign=loading" data-instgrm-version="14" style=" background:#FFF; border:0; border-radius:3px; box-shadow:0 0 1px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.5),0 1px 10px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.15); margin: 1px; max-width:658px; min-width:326px; padding:0; width:99.375%; width:-webkit-calc(100% - 2px); width:calc(100% - 2px);"><div style="padding:16px;"><div style="background-color: #F4F4F4; border-radius: 50%; flex-grow: 0; height: 40px; margin-right: 14px; width: 40px;"></div><div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; flex-grow: 1; justify-content: center;"><div style=" background-color: #F4F4F4; border-radius: 4px; flex-grow: 0; height: 14px; margin-bottom: 6px; width: 100px;"></div><div style=" background-color: #F4F4F4; border-radius: 4px; flex-grow: 0; height: 14px; width: 60px;"></div></div></div><div style="padding: 19% 0;"></div><div style="display:block; height:50px; margin:0 auto 12px; width:50px;"><svg width="50px" height="50px" viewBox="0 0 60 60" version="1.1" xmlns="https://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="https://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"><g stroke="none" stroke-width="1" fill="none" fill-rule="evenodd"><g transform="translate(-511.000000, -20.000000)" fill="#000000"><g><path d="M556.869,30.41 C554.814,30.41 553.148,32.076 553.148,34.131 C553.148,36.186 554.814,37.852 556.869,37.852 C558.924,37.852 560.59,36.186 560.59,34.131 C560.59,32.076 558.924,30.41 556.869,30.41 M541,60.657 C535.114,60.657 530.342,55.887 530.342,50 C530.342,44.114 535.114,39.342 541,39.342 C546.887,39.342 551.658,44.114 551.658,50 C551.658,55.887 546